      "subject": "Mathematics & Geostatistics",
      "topic": "Probability",
      "difficulty": "easy",
      "type": "MCQ",
      "stem": "Two drill holes are tested independently; each strikes ore with probability $0.5$. The probability that at least one strikes ore is",
      "options": [
        "$0.75$",
        "$0.5$",
        "$0.25$",
        "$1.0$"
      ],
      "answer": 0,
      "solution": "**Concept.** $P(\\text{at least one})=1-P(\\text{none})=1-0.5^2$.\n\n**Working.**\n$$1-0.25=0.75.$$\n\n**Answer.** $0.75$",
      "archetype": "B",
      "marks": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "gg-mat-002",
      "subject": "Mathematics & Geostatistics",
      "topic": "Statistics",
      "difficulty": "medium",
      "type": "MCQ",
      "stem": "For a positively skewed assay distribution, which ordering is generally correct?",
      "options": [
        "mode < median < mean",
        "mean < median < mode",
        "mean = median = mode",
        "median < mode < mean"
      ],
      "answer": 0,
      "solution": "**Concept.** Right (positive) skew pulls the mean above the median above the mode.\n\n**Working.**\nmode < median < mean.\n\n**Answer.** mode < median < mean",
      "archetype": "B",
      "marks": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "gg-mat-003",
      "subject": "Mathematics & Geostatistics",
      "topic": "Geostatistics",
      "difficulty": "hard",
      "type": "MSQ",
      "stem": "Which statements about the semivariogram are correct?",
      "options": [
        "The nugget represents micro-scale variability and measurement error",
        "The sill is the variance at which the semivariogram levels off",
        "The range is the lag beyond which samples are correlated",
        "Kriging is an exact interpolator at data points"
      ],
      "answer": [
        0,
        1,
        3
      ],
      "solution": "**Concept.** Nugget = micro-variance; sill = plateau variance; the range is the lag at which correlation VANISHES (beyond the range samples are uncorrelated); kriging honours data.\n\n**Working.**\nOptions 1, 2, 4.\n\n**Answer.** Nugget, sill, kriging-exactness",
      "archetype": "D",
      "marks": 2
    },
